fields.Title: ICE / ANDRE TENT CONTENT
fields.Description: this is where andre's dialogues about the "church/padlock", "who are inside the church" and "tent equipment" are.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, just give me the key." (Get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, just give me the key." (Get the task.)

fields.Title: Andre: ""Brilliant!" He claps his hands. Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Brilliant!" He claps his hands. The air in the tent feels lighter. "Noid, the key!"

fields.Title: Logic: "You're not *completely* satisfied y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're not *completely* satisfied yet.

fields.Title: You: ""Andre, do you know what 'involunta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Andre, do you know what 'involuntary manslaughter' means?"

fields.Title: You: ""Can you tell me more about this ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you tell me more about this machinery?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yeah, yeah! Good to have, bitch to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, yeah! Good to have, bitch to carry. When I first scouted the place I did some reconnaissance. I'm not sure the church even has running water."

fields.Title: Noid: ""What's with the god damn Romangoro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's with the god damn Romangorod Hearings? It's cold, the fluid's for the generator." He points toward the machine.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yeah, totally. I mean... I didn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, totally. I mean... I didn't *personally* see it -- Acele was alone that time, but I believe her. If she comes out running and says there's a crab in there, there's a crab in there."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Sure, why not! Yeah!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, why not! Yeah!"

fields.Title: Volition: "You have to see for yourself. These..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have to see for yourself. These people are not reliable.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Andre: ""Brilliant!" He claps his hands. Th..."]
Reaction Speed: "You sense the trajectory of the lit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You sense the trajectory of the little piece of metal and plastic. The object makes a small ringing sound as it approaches -- just the tiniest chime to your left.

fields.Title: You: ""Right. Other questions." (Conclude..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. Other questions." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: You: ""How can you be sure they haven't s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How can you be sure they haven't starved to death?"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Wow! Looks like there's quite a lot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow! Looks like there's quite a lot there...

fields.Title: You: ""You sound fine to me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You sound fine to me."

fields.Title: You: ""Are you *sure* there was a crab-ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you *sure* there was a crab-man?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Officer, I apologize... Noid doesn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, I apologize... Noid doesn't always understand the joy of giving for the sake of giving. I think it may have something to do with his childhood."

fields.Title: Logic: "Ruby's gone. The woman is someone e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ruby's gone. The woman is someone else.

fields.Title: You: "Be the Cool Cop. Catch the key as i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be the Cool Cop. Catch the key as it flies toward you!

fields.Title: You: "Don't even look at them. You're *th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't even look at them. You're *that* cool. [Leave.]
fields.Alternate1: That's enough glory. At least for now. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Thanks, man." (Play it cool.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thanks, man." (Play it cool.)

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Just felt right. Why, do you want t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just felt right. Why, do you want to be a Tequila *Sunrise?* It's a little too late for that...

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, let's talk about somethin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, let's talk about something else."

fields.Title: Andre: ""When I first scouted the place, ba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When I first scouted the place, back in February, it was abandoned. Empty. Took some time getting the crew together, so about two weeks ago we came here hoping to set the stuff up. Suddenly there are all these strange *machines* lying around in there."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Not that we would know *anything*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not that we would know *anything* about that. Noid just likes to relay stuff."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A stabbing pain. Tears stream uncon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A stabbing pain. Tears stream uncontrollably from your right eye.

fields.Title: Andre: ""It was this dark shape climbing up..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was this dark shape climbing upside down along the ceiling... like some kind of *crab-man*."

fields.Title: You: ""A crab-man?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A crab-man?"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "A pincer manoeuvre."
fields.Dialogue Text: A pincer manoeuvre.

fields.Title: Logic: "So brown and older? Ruby might have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So brown and older? Ruby might have dyed her hair? Though it seems like a stretch at this point.

fields.Title: Logic: "There probably is no crab-man. Don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There probably is no crab-man. Don't let them draw you in with this nonsense.

fields.Title: Drama: "Keep on it, sire."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep on it, sire.

fields.Title: You: ""I changed my mind about the key. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I changed my mind about the key. I'll look into the spookers for you. Just give it to me." (Get the task.)

fields.Title: Andre: ""Not long. Like a week maybe?" He s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not long. Like a week maybe?" He shrugs.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Exactly! That's *exactly* what we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Exactly! That's *exactly* what we thought!"

fields.Title: Andre: ""I knew you'd get it. You're one sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I knew you'd get it. You're one smart cop."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Felt like silence! Awful silence...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Felt like silence! Awful silence..."

fields.Title: You: ""I'll talk to Noid then.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'll talk to Noid then."

fields.Title: You: ""What's that engine starting fluid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's that engine starting fluid for?" (Point to the bottle of "Coupris L'Ange.")
fields.Alternate1: "I get the Nosaphed -- but what about the engine starting fluid?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "Is the amiable speedfreak becoming..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is the amiable speedfreak becoming a bit cross with you? Sounds like it.

fields.Title: Andre: ""The what now?" He leans in to hear..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The what now?" He leans in to hear you better.

fields.Title: Drama: "He's like an actor looking to the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's like an actor looking to the souffleur for his line.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""CRAB-MAN!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "CRAB-MAN!"

fields.Title: You: ""The woman -- red hair maybe? A lor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The woman -- red hair maybe? A lorry-woman?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Must be. Even Cuno knew that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Must be. Even Cuno knew that.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Andre: ""Be careful in there, officer. And..."]
Jump to: [Andre: ""Be careful in there, officer. And..."]
Andre: ""I hope that settles it... or wait...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I hope that settles it... or wait..."

fields.Title: Noid: ""My bad.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "My bad."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Hey now!" He furrows his brow. "I'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey now!" He furrows his brow. "I'm 70% sure they're substance abusers."

fields.Title: You: ""The whatever, I wanted to know abo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The whatever, I wanted to know about another thing."

fields.Title: Andre: ""No idea, man.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No idea, man."

fields.Title: Noid: "The speedfreak nods to you."
fields.Dialogue Text: The speedfreak nods to you.

fields.Title: Noid: ""Only if he promises to look into t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Only if he promises to look into the spookers in the church." He looks at you gravely.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This machinery is of the deeply mys..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This machinery is of the deeply mystical variety.

fields.Title: Logic: "A shrug is good enough for us! Why..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A shrug is good enough for us! Why say it when you can *shrug* it.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "It's as if time has frozen somehow...."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's as if time has frozen somehow. You think you can *sense* the key moving in the air. Yeah, this is gonna be *way* cool.

fields.Title: You: ""What does that even mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What does that even mean?"

fields.Title: Noid: ""I really am sorry, man -- just tak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I really am sorry, man -- just take this, okay?" He pulls out some black paper from his belt-pack.

fields.Title: You: "No, none of this Tequila Sunset bus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, none of this Tequila Sunset business. It's gotten me to death's door. There has to be more in this world...

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Andre, tell him about the feeling!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Andre, tell him about the feeling!"

fields.Title: You: ""But you haven't physically *seen*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you haven't physically *seen* anyone?"

fields.Title: You: ""Hate to tell you, but it reeks of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hate to tell you, but it reeks of sweat in here."

fields.Title: You: ""What engines do you start with it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What engines do you start with it?"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "However, their breathing is regular..."
fields.Dialogue Text: However, their breathing is regular, their jaws stay put, and their pupils aren't dilated. So -- not under the influence right now.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Did you know ethyl ether is used as..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Did you know ethyl ether is used as a light anaesthetic? And a solvent. And an explosive. And for manufacturing amphetamine.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Non-human means a predator."
fields.Dialogue Text: Non-human means a predator.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Well, if you ever decide to change..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, if you ever decide to change your mind, then we're here." He taps the wooden crate he's sitting on. "Just ask me about the door again."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Sure. What?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure. What?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Thank you, we just thought it was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, we just thought it was the right thing to do."

fields.Title: Empathy: "He looks like he's genuinely sorry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks like he's genuinely sorry he didn't throw them better.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Somewhere in the ruinous past that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somewhere in the ruinous past that led you here there was something called 'exams'. You may have learned the term 'involuntary manslaughter' there.

fields.Title: Andre: "He nods attentively, ready to answe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods attentively, ready to answer the questions of 'one smart cop.'

fields.Title: Andre: ""Okay, I'm sorry.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I'm sorry."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm sorry, I'm sorry..." (Bend you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry, I'm sorry..." (Bend your face in *mockery* of his useless contrition.) "You almost *eye-murdered* me -- a cop! That's use of LETHAL FORCE!"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Uhm, which other one? I'm not as i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uhm, which other one? I'm not as in tune with my emotions as you are, Egg."

fields.Title: You: ""About another thing...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "About another thing..."

fields.Title: You: ""It's mixed with a peculiar chemica..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's mixed with a peculiar chemical scent, like laundry detergent..."

fields.Title: Empathy: "For this man even regular silence i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For this man even regular silence is awful enough. But that was... something greater.

fields.Title: Noid: ""Alright." The speedfreak dips into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright." The speedfreak dips into his belt pack and produces a yellow key. He then makes a sudden, cool-infused move, tossing it in your general direction.

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, I catch your drift.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I catch your drift."

fields.Title: Drama: "He appears sincere enough, sire. Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He appears sincere enough, sire. You could of course be wrong.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Uhm... sure." He picks one up from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uhm... sure." He picks one up from the corner and hands it to you. "Here you go, officer -- the Nosa! Blast away!"

fields.Title: Andre: ""I have a major sinus infection. St..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have a major sinus infection. Stuffy nose. We all do. Shit's all blasted up. Winter. Can't even breathe."

fields.Title: Noid: ""Nosaphed *is* the shit!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nosaphed *is* the shit!"

fields.Title: You: ""What was that about some *thing* w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What was that about some *thing* watching you?"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""THE CAGE OF THE RAGE, ROUGH BLAZE!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE CAGE OF THE RAGE, ROUGH BLAZE!"

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Andre: ""Oh, so you met her? Good, good.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, so you met her? Good, good."

fields.Title: You: ""What about the key?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about the key?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Of course. Noid, give the officer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Noid, give the officer the key."

fields.Title: You: ""Jacked up to some *snuff station*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Jacked up to some *snuff station*?"

fields.Title: You: ""All right. Enough of this." (Concl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right. Enough of this." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: You: ""You can't coerce me into taking th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You can't coerce me into taking this on. I don't need the key." (Not now.)

fields.Title: Andre: "He nods enthusiastically. No doubt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods enthusiastically. No doubt a *little* relieved.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Oh, okay." He nods his bleached, s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, okay." He nods his bleached, spiked head. "I won't do that anymore."

fields.Title: You: ""Sounds like nonsense.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sounds like nonsense."

fields.Title: Andre: ""I don't know..." He pauses to thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know..." He pauses to think. "What does anything mean, really?"

fields.Title: You: ""So how can you be sure they're *bu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So how can you be sure they're *burnouts* and *dopeheads* if you haven't even seen them?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""We're getting derailed here. In sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're getting derailed here. In short, you can talk to Noid about the machines. He'll tell you more."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Well, honestly, I can't. But I am.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, honestly, I can't. But I am."

fields.Title: You: ""And it's distilled too.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And it's distilled too."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Mhm?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm?"

fields.Title: You: ""So which one is it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So which one is it?"

fields.Title: Volition: "It feels good to be the smart cop,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It feels good to be the smart cop, doesn't it? That's a good cop to be. Has a nice ring to it. "Smart Cop." You wouldn't want to be "Stupid Cop," now would you? But still -- maybe he's just sucking up to you?

fields.Title: You: ""Wow! You can't. But you do. I shou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow! You can't. But you do. I should add weaponised idiocy to my own repertoire."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "This is a below feeble attempt at a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is a below feeble attempt at avoidance. Basically, he is attempting to weaponise idiocy.

fields.Title: Andre: ""It's for starting engines, man.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's for starting engines, man."
fields.Alternate1: "The engine starting fluid? It's for starting engines."

fields.Title: Andre: "He sniffs the air, then shrugs."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sniffs the air, then shrugs.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Unlike the girl outside, however, t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unlike the girl outside, however, the boys' breathing is regular, their jaws stay put, and their pupils aren't dilated. So they're not under the influence *currently*.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "So he hasn't even been in there lat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So he hasn't even been in there lately? Is he afraid?

fields.Title: You: "Don't ruin the cool by overdoing it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't ruin the cool by overdoing it. Raise your hand in front of your face with minimum effort.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Truth is, I don't really know. Non..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Truth is, I don't really know. None of us do. I don't even know how many there are... all we've seen are glimpses."

fields.Title: Noid: ""Nope.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nope."

fields.Title: Noid: "He is shifting in his spot uncomfor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is shifting in his spot uncomfortably, still feeling sorry for the mishap.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Like... you aren't *alone*, you kn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like... you aren't *alone*, you know?"

fields.Title: Noid: ""But not really," the other one add..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But not really," the other one adds. "Brown hair. Old. Heavy, dark sines."

fields.Title: Andre: ""What Noid said!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What Noid said!"

fields.Title: You: ""You can stop buttering me up now,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You can stop buttering me up now, thank you."

fields.Title: Andre: ""You're right. It *is* nonsense. To..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. It *is* nonsense. Total garbage. I knew you'd see through it, you're one smart cop!"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Don't let all that 'technology' fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't let all that 'technology' fool you." He makes little quotation marks with his fingers when he says *technology*. "Where do you think drugs come from?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't see a single thing wrong w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't see a single thing wrong with that argument."

fields.Title: You: ""What's with all the *Nosaphed*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's with all the *Nosaphed*?"

fields.Title: You: ""Can I have some? I have some nose..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can I have some? I have some nose problems too."

fields.Title: Noid: ""It wasn't quite *human* -- if you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It wasn't quite *human* -- if you know what I mean."

fields.Title: Noid: ""I had to do it in a hurry. Not my..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I had to do it in a hurry. Not my best work... But it should hold for a while."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't need your pity money. Now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't need your pity money. Now where were we?" (Don't take the money.)

fields.Title: Noid: ""One of them has wires running into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "One of them has wires running into bowls of water. Wires. Into *water*. Never seen anything like it."

fields.Title: You: ""Good. Now unto the next thing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. Now unto the next thing."

fields.Title: You: ""Super." (Nod, then let the silence..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Super." (Nod, then let the silence linger.) "And what is ethyl ether anyway?"
fields.Alternate1: "You know, maybe that slight scent of ether I felt before is somehow connected to *ethyl* ether?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Good idea.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good idea."

fields.Title: Drama: "It's like he's lying to you, my lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's like he's lying to you, my liege. But he's slippery enough that there's nothing for you to grab hold of.

fields.Title: Andre: ""I asked Noid to install a measure..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I asked Noid to install a measure against more drifters wandering in. A padlock. It's a temporary fix. Just something to contain the situation."
fields.Alternate1: "I did ask Noid to install a measure against more drifters wandering in. It's a temporary fix. Just something to contain the situation."
fields.Alternate2: "Yes. I asked Noid to install a measure against more drifters wandering in. It's a temporary fix. Just something to contain the situation."

fields.Title: Empathy: "He's not as glad as he would like y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's not as glad as he would like you to think. There's concern in his voice.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "*Ka-ching!* The key hits your palm...."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Ka-ching!* The key hits your palm. The speedfreaks nod to you approvingly.

fields.Title: Andre: ""We were talking about... the padlo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We were talking about... the padlock I think?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""The key..." He cautiously hands yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The key..." He cautiously hands you the yellow keyring.

fields.Title: You: ""That's the least you could do." (T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's the least you could do." (Take the money.)

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yes I do, I listen to Channel 8 al..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes I do, I listen to Channel 8 all the time. I know about crime stuff and I assure you, officer, this is not what's happening here. I'm *at least* 80% sure they're alive. I mean, c'mon -- most people aren't ever that alive in their entire lives!"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Feels nice. It would feel a whole l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Feels nice. It would feel a whole lot less nice had you dropped them, or worse -- got hit in the eye with them. Good thing that didn't happen!

fields.Title: Noid: ""He means like one of those rich-bo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He means like one of those rich-boy private radio stations, where you can listen to people getting killed on. Then jerk off to it... sick shit."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "The gesture is super-futuristic. Go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The gesture is super-futuristic. Goes well with his spiked imbecile-hair.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "At least not under the influence of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At least not under the influence of stimulants. That doesn't rule out: hallucinogens, benzos, some depressants... how do you know all this?

fields.Title: You: "(Point at the bottles of nasal spra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Point at the bottles of nasal spray in the corner.) "The 'Nosaphed Ultra.' You have a lot of it lying around."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Blam! Straight in the eye. Straight..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Blam! Straight in the eye. Straight in the old eye-orb. In *the lookin' ball*!

fields.Title: Authority: "A respectful nod. You proved someth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A respectful nod. You proved something here.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Dammit, take it, don't you just wan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Dammit, take it, don't you just want to see what's *in* there?

fields.Title: You: ""This is cool. Taking initiative li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is cool. Taking initiative like this is proper citizen behaviour and I endorse it."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I'm sorry, too. I guess it wasn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry, too. I guess it wasn't very hard core of us to just lock them in like that."

fields.Title: You: "Where did that come from? Why am I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Where did that come from? Why am I a *Tequila Sunset*?

fields.Title: Andre: ""I'm 70% sure they're substance use..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm 70% sure they're substance users. Don't let the 'technology' fool you." He makes little quotation marks with his fingers when he says *technology*.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yes? What?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes? What?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Oh?" He doesn't know what to say."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh?" He doesn't know what to say.

fields.Title: Andre: ""It's the one they sell at the fuel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's the one they sell at the fuel station."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yeah, you know. The way it was cli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, you know. The way it was climbing up and around the ceiling. Like a crab."

fields.Title: You: "Catch it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Catch it.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Why not! Let's go with that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why not! Let's go with that.

fields.Title: You: ""How long have those people been lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How long have those people been locked in there?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Are you sure? It's probably too lat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Are you sure? It's probably too late to be a Tequila *Sunrise* now.

fields.Title: You: "Damn right I am Tequila Sunset. *Ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Damn right I am Tequila Sunset. *Arriva*!

fields.Title: Noid: ""Man, I'm super sorry. That was tot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Man, I'm super sorry. That was totally my bad, I got overexcited. Threw them too hard. I'm sorry."

fields.Title: You: ""You haven't even seen them and you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You haven't even seen them and you want the police involved?"

fields.Title: You: ""Better safe than sorry. Anything m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Better safe than sorry. Anything more you can tell me?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Oh, and it felt like there was som..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, and it felt like there was some *thing* in there with us, watching us from the dark..."

fields.Title: You: ""There was another thing...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "There was another thing..."

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, okay, I guess that makes sense..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, okay, I guess that makes sense. Tell me about another thing."

fields.Title: Noid: ""Told you we have a smell problem."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Told you we have a smell problem." He picks up a piece of telephone cord and inspects it.

fields.Title: Andre: ""Ether? I don't smell ether. Do you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ether? I don't smell ether. Do you, Noid?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""I guess it does.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess it does."

fields.Title: Logic: "It doesn't take a forensic scientis..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It doesn't take a forensic scientist to guess it's drug-related. They look and act like the kind of guys who've done their fair share.

fields.Title: Noid: "The young man with ribcage-shaped s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The young man with ribcage-shaped suspenders looks at you standing there -- with a goofy grin on your face.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "*Not human*? As in a ghost? *Do* yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Not human*? As in a ghost? *Do* you know what he means?

fields.Title: You: ""Ambush behaviour." (Nod.) "Crab-ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ambush behaviour." (Nod.) "Crab-man."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Odd. Crabs are usually marine creat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Odd. Crabs are usually marine creatures. And not known for climbing walls.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The implications of this are... too..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The implications of this are... too numerous to consider. Proceed with caution. Learn all you can before entering that dark building.

fields.Title: Andre: ""I'm super sure they're alive. I me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm super sure they're alive. I mean, c'mon! I'm at least 90%... maybe 85% sure they're still alive."

fields.Title: Noid: "Noid watches you pick up the key wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Noid watches you pick up the key with a smirk.

fields.Title: You: ""Eighty-five percent is good enough..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Eighty-five percent is good enough. No one lives forever, baby!"

fields.Title: You: ""I get by. Now where was I with tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I get by. Now where was I with that padlock..."

fields.Title: Andre: ""You should talk to Noid about that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You should talk to Noid about that. I just got a distinct *burnout* and *dopehead* sine from them. Probably jacked up to some snuff station too. Probably, very likely."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yes," he leans in for emphasis, "t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes," he leans in for emphasis, "there's also *the machinery*..."

fields.Title: You: ""I see you brought your own water.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I see you brought your own water."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait. I also smell ether. Why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait. I also smell ether. Why?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Yes!" He nods energetically. "That..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes!" He nods energetically. "That's all Nosaphed's doing. Without the Nosa I'd be drowning in shit right now."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Glimpses? Who are these people, sec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Glimpses? Who are these people, secret agents? Stealth operatives?

fields.Title: Jump to: [Andre: ""Be careful in there, officer. And..."]
You: "(With your hand on your eye, pick u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (With your hand on your eye, pick up the keys.) "I'm getting too old for this. Where were we?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "The word *august* used as an adject..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The word *august* used as an adjective -- that's how cool it feels to be old and cool in the eyes of the young. Let's face it, you're near death yet bathed in the golden rays of stately grandeur. Like a late summer's day. Like a Daddy-O...

fields.Title: You: ""Ouch! Goddamn asshole... what is W..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ouch! Goddamn asshole... what is WRONG with you?! Can't you see I'm in PAIN now?!"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Man up! It's nothing. Pick the godd..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Man up! It's nothing. Pick the goddamn key up, put it in your pocket, and move on.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""No! The other one.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No! The other one."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Not exactly. We've just seen someo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not exactly. We've just seen someone who we think is a woman go in and out of the church. A couple of times. And we felt someone... or some *thing*... eyeing us inside. But... that's kinda it."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "With a small surge of PEA, alertnes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With a small surge of PEA, alertness fills you. As if to say: This is a dark corner, look behind it!

fields.Title: You: ""Good. Now, about another thing...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. Now, about another thing..."

fields.Title: Noid: ""It was stalking Acele. Exhibiting..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was stalking Acele. Exhibiting ambush behaviour."

fields.Title: Noid: ""Egg means the situation is monitor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Egg means the situation is monitored." The man nods grimly. "It's 'relatively' safe. No one has died yet."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Sure, man. Tell us what you wanna..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, man. Tell us what you wanna know, let's do it!"

fields.Title: You: "Bask in the glory."
fields.Dialogue Text: Bask in the glory.

fields.Title: You: "Let it fall to the ground, then pic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let it fall to the ground, then pick it up. Like a normal adult person.

fields.Title: You: ""Eight-five percent is not good eno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Eight-five percent is not good enough when you're dealing with another person's physical well-being."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Of course you are! It's too late to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course you are! It's too late to be a Tequila *Sunrise* now... there will be no sunrise, not for you.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Like a Tequila Sunset."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a Tequila Sunset.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""*Oh yeah...*" He looks at his frie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Oh yeah...*" He looks at his friend with an expression of profound understanding.

fields.Title: Noid: ""Me too... I shouldn't have that ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Me too... I shouldn't have that kind of power over another person. I'm not the one with the violence monopoly here -- you are. I'm glad that key is out of my hands now."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Well..." he leans in for emphasis,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well..." he leans in for emphasis, "there's also *the machinery*..."

fields.Title: Andre: ""It does, doesn't it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It does, doesn't it?"

fields.Title: You: ""How's that extra high ether conten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How's that extra high ether content working out for you? Does it do the trick?
fields.Alternate1: "Relax. How's that extra high ether content working out for you? Does it do the trick?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""Oh! The old 'Ultra'... we.... uhm...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh! The old 'Ultra'... we.... uhm..."

fields.Title: Noid: ""You should ask her about it -- but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You should ask her about it -- but be nice. Don't tell her you don't believe in the crab."
